</form><html xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:math="java.lang.Math" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:xs="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:fo="http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Format" xmlns:fn="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-functions" xmlns:xdt="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-datatypes" xmlns:caml="http://lc.ca.gov/legalservices/schemas/caml.1#" xmlns:xhtml="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><head><title>AB2229:v98#DOCUMENT</title><meta name="dc:identifier" content="AB2229"/><meta name="dc:title" content="AB &#xA;              2229-&#xA;                AMENDED&#xA;              "/><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html;charset=utf-8"/></head><body><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Start</h2></span><div id="bill_all" align="justify"><div id="about"><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><table style="border-collapse: collapse" cellSpacing="0" align="center" role="presentation"><tbody><tr><td align="center"><span style=" text-transform: uppercase; font-size: 1em">
                Revised
              </span> <span style="text-transform: uppercase">April 08, 2026</span><br/></td></tr></tbody><tbody><tr><td align="center"><span style=" text-transform: uppercase; font-size: 1em">
                Amended
               IN </span><span style=" text-transform: uppercase; font-size: 1em">
                Assembly
              </span> <span style="text-transform: uppercase">March 25, 2026</span><br/></td></tr></tbody><tbody><tr><td align="center"/></tr></tbody></table></div><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><font size="3" style="FONT-FAMILY: MinionPC, Arial Unicode MS">
                    CALIFORNIA LEGISLATURE—
                    2025–2026 REGULAR SESSION</font></div><br clear="all"/><span id="bill_house_num"><div style="float: left; width:50%; font-weight: bold; "><span style="text-transform: uppercase; text-align:left;width:50%;"><b>
                Assembly Bill
              </b></span></div><div style="float:right; width:50%; text-align:right;"><span style="text-transform: uppercase;"><b>No. 2229</b></span></div></span><hr/><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><table style="border-collapse: collapse" cellSpacing="0" align="center" role="presentation"><tbody><tr><td id="bill_authors" align="center"><span style="font-weight:bold;">Introduced by Assembly Member Pellerin<br/><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>(Coauthors: Assembly Members Fong and Jeff Gonzalez)<br/></i></font></span></td></tr><tr><td id="bill_intro_date" align="center" class="textcenter"><br/>February 19, 2026</td></tr></tbody></table></div><hr/><br clear="all"/><div id="title"><span style="font-weight:normal;font-size:0.9em;">An act to add Chapter 4.5 (commencing with Section 89427) to Part 55 of Division 8 of Title 3 of the Education Code, relating to the California State University.</span></div><br clear="all"/><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><h2>LEGISLATIVE COUNSEL'S DIGEST</h2></div><br/><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0"><span id="subject">AB 2229, as amended, Pellerin.
                          The California State University Enrollment, Access, and Retention of<font color="#B30000"><strike> Nontraditional</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> Noncontinuous</i></font> Students Program.</span></div><div><span id="digesttext"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Existing law establishes the California State University, under the administration of the Trustees of the California State University, as one of the segments of public postsecondary education in the state. Existing law requires the California State University to require each campus in its system to grant students the right to reenroll in their baccalaureate degree program after withdrawing or stopping out, if the student was in good academic standing with the university.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">This bill would establish the California State University Enrollment, Access, and Retention of<font color="#B30000"><strike> Nontraditional</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> Noncontinuous</i></font> Students Program to increase the reenrollment rates of California
		State University students who have withdrawn from a campus before the conferral of a baccalaureate degree. The bill would require the Chancellor of the California State University to adopt a policy prioritizing enrollment funding for California State University campuses that meet enrollment figures and engage in outreach to reenroll former California State University students. The bill would require, on or before July 1, 2027, the trustees to adopt a policy related to evaluating transcripts of<font color="#B30000"><strike> nontraditional</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> noncontinuous</i></font> students who wish to reenroll in the California State University, as specified. The bill would require each campus to designate, on or before July 1, 2027, a<font color="#B30000"><strike> nontraditional</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>
		noncontinuous</i></font> student advisor, and, commencing July 1, 2027, provide priority registration to<font color="#B30000"><strike> nontraditional</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> noncontinuous</i></font> students returning to complete a degree. The bill would require, on or before September 1, 2028, the trustees to maintain an internet-accessible data dashboard that includes, among other things, the number of<font color="#B30000"><strike> nontraditional</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> noncontinuous</i></font> students who have reenrolled at a campus.</div></span></div><span class="hidden"><h2>Digest Key</h2></span><span id="vote">
      Vote:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">MAJORITY</span>  </span><span id="appropriation">
      Appropriation:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">NO</span>  </span><span id="fiscalcommittee">
      Fiscal Committee:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">YES</span>  </span><span id="localprogram">
      Local Program:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">NO</span>  </span></div><hr/><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Text</h2></span><div id="bill"><div style=" text-transform: uppercase"><h2 style=" text-align: left;">The people of the State of California do enact as follows:</h2><br/></div><div id="s10.259682626517335"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0" class="ActionLine"><h3 style="font-weight:bold; display:inline;">SECTION 1.</h3> Chapter 4.5 (commencing with Section 89427) is added to Part 55 of Division 8 of Title 3 of the Education Code, to read:</div><div><div><div id="id_55E2F285-5AD0-4674-AC09-455915BE4676"><div><h5 style="text-align:left;">
                CHAPTER
               4.5. The California State University Enrollment, Access, and Retention of<font color="#B30000"><strike> Nontraditional</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> Noncontinuous</i></font>Students Program</h5></div></div><div><p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"><h6 style="display:inline;">89427.</h6> As used in this chapter, the following definitions apply:</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(a) “Campus” means a campus of the California State University.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(b) <font color="#B30000"><strike>“Nontraditional </strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>“Noncontinuous </i></font>student” means a student who was previously enrolled at a campus of the California State University and withdrew before the conferral of a baccalaureate<font color="#B30000"><strike> degree.</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> degree, excluding students who
					 withdrew due to pending academic disqualification or pending disciplinary expulsion.</i></font></div></p></div><div><p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"><h6 style="display:inline;">89428.</h6> (a) The California State University Enrollment, Access, and Retention of<font color="#B30000"><strike> Nontraditional</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> Noncontinuous</i></font> Students Program is hereby established to increase the reenrollment rates of<font color="#B30000"><strike> nontraditional</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> noncontinuous</i></font> students.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(b) The Chancellor of the California State University shall adopt a policy to prioritize enrollment funding to campuses that meet enrollment figures and
					 engage in outreach efforts to reenroll former California State University students who may have withdrawn from a campus, as part of the campuses’ retention and enrollment efforts.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(c) On or before July 1, 2027, the trustees, in collaboration with the Academic Senate of the California State University, shall adopt a policy related to the evaluation of transcripts of<font color="#B30000"><strike> nontraditional</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> noncontinuous</i></font> students who wish to reenroll in the California State University. The policy shall ensure that the evaluation of transcripts does all of the following:</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(1) If a period of five years or less has elapsed since the student enrolled in coursework, accepts all California State University coursework as
					 applicable to a degree in the original field of study the student was attempting before withdrawing from the campus.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(2) If a period of more than five years has elapsed since the student enrolled in coursework, both of the following:</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 2.5em;">(A) Accepts all the lower division general education California State University courses regardless of the time<font color="#B30000"><strike> lapse</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> lapsed</i></font> between the student’s reenrollment.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 2.5em;">(B) For upper division California State University applicable courses, maximizes credit to the student for degree completion and minimizes time to degree.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(3) Prohibits
					 requiring a student to repeat California State University coursework already completed with a satisfactory grade.</div><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(4) For California Community College courses taken after enrollment at the California State University, maximizes credit to the student for degree completion and minimizes time to degree.</div></i></font><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(d) (1) On or before July 1, 2027, each campus shall designate one<font color="#B30000"><strike> nontraditional</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>
					 noncontinuous</i></font> student advisor for the campus to do both of the following:</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 2.5em;">(A) Assist with the implementation of the policy adopted pursuant to subdivision (c).</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 2.5em;">(B) Provide<font color="#B30000"><strike> nontraditional</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> noncontinuous</i></font> students with academic advising and support services to help the students enroll in coursework that optimizes their ability to complete their intended major.<font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> To the extent possible, the advisor shall provide the noncontinuous student with a course map to graduation.</i></font></div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(2) This
					 subdivision shall not be interpreted to require a campus to hire a new advisor to comply with the requirements of this subdivision.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(e) Commencing July 1, 2027, each campus shall provide priority registration to a<font color="#B30000"><strike> nontraditional</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> noncontinuous</i></font> student who is returning to complete a baccalaureate degree.</div></p></div><div><p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"><h6 style="display:inline;">89429.</h6> On or before September 1, 2028, the trustees shall maintain an internet-accessible data dashboard that includes all of the following:</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(a) The number of<font color="#B30000"><strike> nontraditional</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> noncontinuous</i></font> students who have reenrolled at a campus.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(b) Program participation demographics, including all of the following:</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(1) Student race and ethnicity.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(2) Whether a student is a federal Pell Grant recipient, as
					 available.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(3) Whether a student is a first-generation college student.</div><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(4) Whether a student is a Cal Grant recipient.</div></i></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(5) Whether a student is a Middle Class Scholarship recipient pursuant to Article 22 (commencing with Section 70020) of Chapter 2 of Part 42 of Division 5.</div></i></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(6) The number of community college classes taken after the student withdrew from the California State University and before they reenrolled at the California State University.</div></i></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(7) The time period between the student’s withdrawal and reenrollment at the California State University.</div></i></font><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(c) (1) The time-to-degree rates and completion rates for<font color="#B30000"><strike> nontraditional</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> noncontinuous</i></font> students.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(2) The full-time enrollment equivalent of the information described in paragraph (1) may also be included.</div></p></div></div></div></div><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i></i></font></div><div align="center"><span class="CorrectionsSeparator">___________________</span></div><br/><br/><span class="CorrectionsHeading"><span class="Correction">
	 REVISIONS:</span><br/><span class="Correction">
	 Heading—Line 2.</span><br/></span><div align="center"><span class="CorrectionsSeparator">___________________</span></div></div></body></html>
